createTable.name: createTable
createTable.help: Creates a datatable with a list of columns, and 1 or more empty rows. To populate the rows, use `mapColumn` or `mathColumn`.

mapColumn.name: mapColumn
mapColumn.help: Adds a column calculated as the result of other columns. Changes are made only when you provide arguments.See also `alterColumn` and `staticColumn`.

id.name: id
id.help: An optional id of the resulting column. When no id is provided, the id will be looked up from the existing column by the provided name argument. If no column with this name exists yet, a new column with this name and an identical id will be added to the table.

name.name: name
name.help: The name of the resulting column. Names are not required to be unique.

expression.name: expression
expression.help: An expression that is executed on every row, provided with a single-row `datatable` context and returning the cell value.

copyMetaFrom.name: copyMetaFrom
copyMetaFrom.help: If set, the meta object from the specified column id is copied over to the specified target column. If the column doesn't exist it silently fails.

math.name: math
math.help: Interprets a `TinyMath` math expression using a `number` or `datatable` as _context_. The `datatable` columns are available by their column name. If the _context_ is a number it is available as `value`.

onError.name: onError
onError.help: In case the `TinyMath` evaluation fails or returns NaN, the return value is specified by onError. When `'throw'`, it will throw an exception, terminating expression execution (default).

mathColumn.name: mathColumn
mathColumn.help: Adds a column calculated as the result of other columns. Changes are made only when you provide arguments.See also `alterColumn` and `staticColumn`.

onError.name: onError
onError.help: In case the `TinyMath` evaluation fails or returns NaN, the return value is specified by onError. When `'throw'`, it will throw an exception, terminating expression execution (default).

id.name: id
id.help: id of the resulting column. Must be unique.

name.name: name
name.help: The name of the resulting column. Names are not required to be unique.

copyMetaFrom.help: If set, the meta object from the specified column id is copied over to the specified target column. If the column doesn't exist it silently fails.

border.name: border

fill.help: An SVG color to fill the shape.

maintainAspect.name: maintainAspect
maintainAspect.help: Maintain the shape's original aspect ratio?

image.name: image
image.help: The image to reveal. Provide an image asset as a `base64` data URL, or pass in a sub-expression.

emptyImage.name: emptyImage
emptyImage.help: An optional background image to reveal over. Provide an image asset as a ``base64`` data URL, or pass in a sub-expression.

origin.name: origin
origin.help: The position to start the image fill. For example, `"top"`, `"bottom"`, `"left"`, or right.

emptyImage.name: emptyImage
emptyImage.help: Fills the difference between the _context_ and `max` parameter for the element with this image. Provide an image asset as a `base64` data URL, or pass in a sub-expression.

image.name: image
image.help: The image to repeat. Provide an image asset as a `base64` data URL, or pass in a sub-expression.

max.name: max
max.help: The maximum number of times the image can repeat.

size.name: size
size.help: The maximum height or width of the image, in pixels. When the image is taller than it is wide, this function limits the height.

image.name: image
image.help: Displays an image. Provide an image asset as a `base64` data URL, or pass in a sub-expression.

dataurl.name: dataurl
dataurl.help: The HTTP(S) URL or `base64` data URL of an image.

mode.name: mode
mode.help: `"contain"` shows the entire image, scaled to fit. `"cover"` fills the container with the image, cropping from the sides or bottom as needed. `"stretch"` resizes the height and width of the image to 100% of the container.

demodata.name: demodata

type.name: type
type.help: The name of the demo data set to use.

pointseries.name: pointseries
pointseries.help: Turn a `datatable` into a point series model. Currently we differentiate measure from dimensions by looking for a `TinyMath` expression. See https://www.elastic.co/guide/en/kibana/current/canvas-tinymath-functions.html. If you enter a `TinyMath` expression in your argument, we treat that argument as a measure, otherwise it is a dimension. Dimensions are combined to create unique keys. Measures are then deduplicated by those keys using the specified `TinyMath` function

color.name: color
color.help: An expression to use in determining the mark's color.

size.name: size
size.help: The size of the marks. Only applicable to supported elements.

text.name: text
text.help: The text to show on the mark. Only applicable to supported elements.
